It is funny that the USSR did not want to have nuclear warheads on its own territory for security or speed reasons due to its western location.
Only the warheads were stored in the underground shelters (there are two in each maple tree), not the entire missile, as it is said.
If it was necessary to deploy this weapon, a special unit would arrive, pick up the head and mount it on some kind of carrier.
