The man from Hroby "shot" his girlfriend from Kostomlaty
The man from Hrob unwittingly helped the police officers to secure his nationally wanted girlfriend from Kostomlat, for whom an arrest warrant had been issued.
He summoned her himself.
But he went about it in a roundabout way.
First, he approached a passerby and made up a story that he had been robbed.
Officers responded to the 911 call and were amazed when the alleged "victim" told them he had made the whole thing up to get the officers to respond to the scene.
In fact, he just wanted to ask the police officers how to file a report with the Police of the Czech Republic.
When the officers checked the identity of the man and his girlfriend, they discovered that the woman was on the national wanted list and a warrant for her arrest had been issued.
The case is therefore being dealt with by the police.
