The Bethlehem flame is in the Czech Republic; the scouts have taken it from Austria
Břeclav – The flame lit in Bethlehem, where, according to Christian tradition, Jesus Christ was born, is in the Czech Republic.
This time, however, the scouts did not go to Vienna due to the coronavirus pandemic; in the morning, they received it from their Austrian colleagues at the Reintal – Břeclav border crossing.
They accepted it at the border last year as well.
The Bethlehem Light is a beautiful Christmas tradition we participate in every year, and I look forward to it very much.
I am honoured to have been chosen, said scout Amálie Budíková to the present journalists.
While last year the handover took place at the Mikulov-Drasenhofen border crossing, directly on the border bridge, this year it took place at the Reintal-Břeclav border crossing in the car park.
However, the scouts usually travel by train to Vienna.
The delivery of the flame across the Czech Republic will not change.
The scouts set off with the Bethlehem light by train to Brno, where they will hand it over to the diocesan bishop Vojtěch Cikrle.
Scout couriers will deliver the light on Saturday, 18 December. They will travel by selected express trains and passenger trains.
The light will then be taken over by the local scouts or volunteers, who will then spread the flame across the Czech Republic, even to places where the trains do not go.
Even this year, scouts must follow the current measures to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.
It is going the same way as last year.
We are recommending that the delivery teams and local event organisers, of course, wear masks, try to keep their distance, be as few as possible, not sing with their colleagues, in short, to behave in a way that is as safe as possible, said the spokesperson for the Bethlehem Light event, Zuzana Hrbková.
The tradition of the Bethlehem Light, which travels through Europe, was born in 1986 in Austria.
The aim is to spread the idea of peace, friendship and peace at the same time as the flame.
For believers, the light of Bethlehem is a symbol of hope, a light that overcomes the darkness.
In the Czech Republic, the scouts and scouts have been taking care of its dissemination for more than 30 years.
The event is organised by hundreds of volunteers, and the flame is therefore also a symbol of selflessness and human solidarity.
All the news, including a list of places where people can get a candle, can be found on the website www.betlemskesvetlo.cz.
