According to the law, Covid is on the list of infectious diseases.
That is, in the same group as HIV, the plague, yellow fever or typhus.
§ 152 Dissemination of a contagious human disease
(1) Whoever willfully causes or increases the danger of introduction or spread of an infectious disease among people shall be punished by imprisonment for a term of six months to three years, by a fine, or by confiscation of property.
(2) The perpetrator will be sentenced to imprisonment for a term of two to eight years,
(c) breaches an important duty arising from his employment, profession, position or function, or imposed on him by law, or
(d) causing serious injury by such an act.
(3) The perpetrator shall be punished with a prison sentence of three to ten years if, in the act referred to in paragraph 1, he has caused serious bodily harm to at least two persons or death.
(4) The perpetrator will be sentenced to imprisonment for five to twelve years, if the act referred to in paragraph 1 results in the death of at least two people.
