The Commission has already delayed approval of Poland's plan to tap 36 billion euros from the EU's recovery fund to revive economies hit by the COVID-19 pandemic.
And it is under pressure from the European Parliament to move forward and use a mechanism to withdraw EU funding from countries that break the rule-of-law principles.
