Vicki Holland of the UK tortured the capuchin monkey Milly
Horrific footage shows the moment a terrified monkey cowered in a toilet bowl before her heartless owner flushed her down and laughed at her.
Holland fed the monkey hot dogs, kebabs, and hamburgers, regardless of its actual nutritional needs.
Magistrates in Gwent have now banned her for life from keeping animals, The Sun reports.
The primate rehabilitation experts caring for Milly after her ordeal have said they have never seen a spaceman so scared.
Milly spent almost two years in rehabilitation at Monkey World in Dorset and is now happily playing with another rescued monkey called Moon.
The mother-of-four admitted two charges of causing unnecessary suffering to a protected animal.
She was sentenced to a 12-week prison sentence, suspended for one year, at Gwent Magistrates' Court.
Holland was also sentenced to 120 hours of unpaid community service, banned for life from keeping animals, and must pay 12,000 Czech crowns in court costs.
Steph Sawyer, who led the Small Monkeys team that rehabilitated the abused animal, said: "Milly is doing well but her rehabilitation will continue."
Milly took a while to get used to people again.
