After years of decline and suppression of this illegal business, MLM recruiting is back in the limelight.
I was one of the recruits, I tried it (I was 20 years old, first year at university), the initial promises of product training and business skills quickly turned into "you don't need to care about that, just get people on board".
I was genuinely interested in the products I was selling, as I wanted to help people, but the training was more about how to scare and talk people into buying.
