New timetables come into effect in Prague from Sunday, mainly affecting suburban services
Passengers in Prague's integrated transport system (PID) can look forward to several changes from Sunday, which will affect mainly suburban services.
New lines were created, some changed their routes, and others ceased to exist.
Mladoboleslavsko is now joining the integrated system.
From Sunday, fast trains from České Budějovice will stop in Zahradní Město in the capital.
S7 suburban trains will run on the route from Beroun to Český Brod, passing through Prague's main station.
The recently opened station in Prague-Zahradní Město will now be served by the R17 express train from České Budějovice and Benešov.
The PID will now be extended to other areas.
Among other things, the buses will go as far as Světlá nad Sázavou, Blatno near Jesenice, Staré Splavy and Turnov.
Buses in the Mladá Boleslav region will be included, including lines that cross into the Liberec and Královéhradecký regions.
During the integration, 77 lines will be cancelled, 37 new ones will be introduced and the operation of 12 existing lines will be modified.
A new bus line 405 will run from Prague's Zličín to Žatec.
A new direct connection between Prague and Kralovice near Rakovník has also been established, replacing the discontinued S53 train line.
Services from Prague to Rakovník will be strengthened in the morning rush hour and on weekends, with the new express line number 404.
Lines 400 and 410 running to the Liberec Region are now included in the PID system.
They depart from the Střížkov metro station, not from the Nádraží Holešovice station.
Line 400 runs through Mělník, Dubou and Česká Lípa to Nový Bor, and selected services continue to Rumburk or Cvikov.
The supplementary line 410 goes through Mělník and Dubá to Doksy, Mimoň and Jablonné v Podještědí.
On the other hand, the operation of dozens of local lines in Central Bohemia has been cancelled or restricted, including lines to Mochov, Dobříš, and Rožmitál pod Třemšínem.
All trains leaving Prague at 02:30 have been cancelled.
Due to the modernisation of the railway, there are long-term restrictions on the lines Prague – Beroun, Prague – Lysá nad Labem and around Kolín.
Changes await passengers at other locations as well.
Buses are replacing some of the cancelled train lines, or the section of the 420 line from Dobříš with a connection from Prague, where it is possible to use PID tickets all the way to Milevsko.
Changes were made to the routes of lines 540 to 543 in Nymburk, and the routes of some buses on the border of Central Bohemia and Hořovicko in the Plzeň Region have been adjusted.
