Agent Tesla is terrorising pre-Christmas Czechia.
While October data showed a slight decline in attack campaigns, last month saw a marked increase in attacks as the year drew to a close.
We recorded a large campaign in relation to Agent Tesla on November 18.
The attacks are specifically aimed at the Czech Republic.
The strategy of the attackers remains the same for the time being.
The infected attachment in the email is designed to get the user's attention with a name that refers to payments and financial transactions.
While last month the dangerous attachment had the word "invoice" in its name, this time it was marked as "Copy of invoice for 11,2021...exe," said Martin Jirkal from Eset.
The spyware has features that scan web browsers and other programs, such as Microsoft Outlook, Mozilla Thunderbird, and Yandex email clients.
The malicious code actively searches for stored credentials, which are then sent to the attackers.
The last major campaign in the Czech Republic took place at the end of August and beginning of September, and as the holidays and the end of the year approach, the activity of the attackers is once again on the rise.
In November, the Formbook spyware remained active.
Unlike Agent Tesla, in this case the attackers are not specifically targeting the Czech Republic, and security specialists have recorded global campaigns in November.
Compared to the October Formbook figures, it has slightly weakened in November, but it is still responsible for nearly a fifth of all detections.
The attacks were continuous throughout the month with heightened activity on the 3rd, 10th, and 15th of November.
The formbook usually contained an attachment with the .exe extension named REQUEST FOR SPECIFICATION.
However, the term "invoice" continues to be used.
The attachment in Czech may be much more dangerous for a Czech user.
Security analysts have observed a significant decline and dampening of activity in the Fareit program, which was responsible for 1.6 per cent of attacks and had no major offensive campaign in the Czech Republic in recent months.
